Subject: Re: [T2] removing stickers

Hi Brian,

Along with goo-gone, a hair dryer is also a big help. Warm adhesive will be
a lot more pliable and less likely to take underlying paint up with it.

It's a very common technique working on motorcycle decals.

Happy trails,

Greg Potts
1973/74/79 Westfakia Conversion  **Bob the Tomato **
http://www.pottsfamily.ca/westfakia
